All Classes

  • All Classes Class Summary Enum Summary 
    Class Description
    Genome
    A Genome is a representation of a code block in our C program.
    GenomeWriter
    This class writes the evolved genome snippets to the given .h file at given positions.
    Incubator
    The incubator, where the genetic programming algorithms are held.
    Message
    A class that wraps around the datagrams received from the server.
    Overseer
    This class oversees the generation of new populations and the execution of said population's resulting c file.
    Population
    The population used for the DeathRace genetic programming.
    Server
    A class for a simple server, this server only receives UDP datagrams from the master compitition process.
    Snippet
    An enumeration of the available code snippets, represented as numbers 1 - n in a map and accessed by a public getSnippet method.
